1. How to merge fork's origin changes to your local branch.

a) check out remote branch from upstreams 
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1783405/git-checkout-remote-branch
b)  fetch and merge remote upstreams changes to your local
https://help.github.com/articles/fork-a-repo

c) the upstream author just merge the pull request similar to 
https://help.github.com/articles/using-pull-requests
